ChatGPT said:
Hereâ€™s the concise truth about Tailscaleâ€™s open-source status and how that affects building a micropayments web like the one youâ€™re working on:

ğŸ§  1) Is Tailscale open-source?
Partially â€” yes.

The Tailscale client (daemon that runs on your devices) is open source â€” you can build it yourself for Linux, Android, and more.

The DERP relay server code is also open source.

However, the coordination server (the cloud service that manages identities, key exchange, and tailnet coordination) is closed source and run by Tailscale Inc. 

So:
âœ” Most of the networking code youâ€™d care about is open.
âœ˜ The central server that makes the network â€œeasyâ€ is proprietary. 

ğŸ›  2) Do you need Tailscale to build the micropayment web?
Not necessarily.

Tailscale is very convenient because:

