4. The UTXO model: sovereignty at the transaction level
Why is this important? Because sovereignty isnâ€™t abstract â€” it lives in the mechanics of money and contracts.

Each UTXO in BSV represents a discrete, independently verifiable right to spend value.

Transactions cannot be changed retroactively; they are cryptographically locked.

Anyone interacting with the ledger can verify ownership, movement, and validity without relying on third parties.

This means sovereignty is built into the system itself, not just claimed rhetorically. For governments, this is gold: itâ€™s final, auditable, and enforceable sovereignty. For individuals, itâ€™s confidence: your rights and value are independent of any single authority.

