Blog Post â€” â€œKintsugi API: Pay-per-Call AI with BSV and Headscaleâ€
Title: Unlock AI Access, Pay-per-Call, on Your Own Private Network

Introduction:
The AI revolution is here â€” but access is often expensive, gated behind subscriptions, or trapped behind centralized services. At b0ase.com, weâ€™ve designed Kintsugi API, a micropayment-gated AI chat service powered by BitcoinSV and designed to work with private networks like Headscale.

The Idea
Imagine paying per AI call, instead of buying a monthly plan. Each request is small, auditable, and instantly settled via BSV micropayments. Kintsugi tracks every usage unit, giving you real-time visibility of AI consumption.

Need a single prompt answered? 0.001 BSV.

Need to run a series of prompts for an incubator cohort? Pay only for what you use.

How It Works
User sends prompt â†’ /v1/chat endpoint

Payment validated â†’ micropayment token checked via BSV

AI responds â†’ ClawedBot routes call to Claude Max

Usage recorded â†’ logs + balance updated

Optional: private network access via Headscale

Business Model Integration with Headscale
Private AI networks: Enterprises or incubators can run Kintsugi nodes on Headscale VPNs, restricting access to authorized teams.

Auditable usage: Every call is tracked and reconciled in your own private network.

Micropayment flexibility: Users top up balances with BSV, giving a new revenue layer without credit cards or centralized billing.

Essentially, Kintsugi + Headscale allows private, permissioned AI networks monetized via micropayments, replacing bloated subscription models with efficient, pay-as-you-go access.

Why This Matters
Security: API keys never exposed, endpoints sandboxed

Flexibility: Individual or team usage, pay-per-call, or tiered balances

Scalability: Can expand to multiple AI models and enterprise deployments

Sovereignty: Your data, your network, your payments â€” powered by BitcoinSV

Conclusion
Kintsugi is the first step toward micropayment-powered AI networks. With BSV handling payments and Headscale enabling private, controlled access, you can finally own your AI infrastructure, pay only for what you use, and scale securely.

The future of AI access is private, pay-per-use, and auditable â€” and Kintsugi makes it real.

