Core axis: eligibility offset
Let:

n = the event at which a token is issued (or bought)

Dividends are paid from event n + k

Where k defines the scheme.

That gives you a clean, extensible naming system.

Scheme 1: Immediate Eligibility
n+0 Dividend Scheme
Definition
A token is eligible to receive dividends from the same transaction that creates it.

Properties

