Scheme 2: Delayed Eligibility
n+1 Dividend Scheme
Definition
A token becomes eligible for dividends only from the next payment onward.

Properties

First buyer receives nothing until someone else uses the system

Real exposure to demand

Still rewards early participation

Removes self-rebates

Plain-language description

â€œYou earn from others using the system, not from yourself joining it.â€

Economic character

Positive risk

Clean price discovery

Logarithmic, bounded upside

Market prices reflect future demand

Good for

Real products

Educational demos that donâ€™t lie

Tokenised infrastructure narratives

Anything you might actually deploy

This is the one you build if youâ€™re serious.

Extending the schema (future-proofing)
Now you have a clean ladder.

n+2 Dividend Scheme
Token earns only after two subsequent events

Dampens speculation further

Strongly privileges long-term adoption

Useful for:

public infrastructure

anti-gaming environments

n+k General Form
Eligibility after k future events

k can be:

fixed

time-based

volume-based

Turns this into a tunable economic instrument

Optional naming (human-friendly aliases)
You can use both numeric + human names in the blog.

Scheme	Technical Name	Human Name
