What does â€œ+*â€ actually mean?
â€œ*â€ is partial eligibility.

Instead of:

0% â†’ 100% eligibility at a discrete step

You get:

0% â†’ x% â†’ 100% eligibility over time or activity

So eligibility becomes continuous, not binary.

Thatâ€™s the whole idea.

A clean definition
n+1+ Dividend Scheme*
Definition
A token becomes eligible for dividends starting at event n+1, but its share of dividends ramps up gradually, according to a defined function.

* is a fractional participation weight, not a second token.

Why this matters (structurally)
Binary eligibility creates cliffs:

speculation at boundaries

gaming of timing

hard-to-explain â€œwhy now?â€ moments

Fractional eligibility:

smooths incentives

reduces timing arbitrage

better reflects commitment over time

This is exactly how grown-up financial instruments behave.

Three sensible ways to define â€œ*â€
Here are the three versions that actually make sense. Everything else is noise.

1ï¸âƒ£ Time-weighted ramp
(n+1+t)

A token earns:

0% immediately after purchase

ramps to 100% over time (e.g. days, weeks, months)

Interpretation

â€œOwnership matures.â€

Properties

discourages flipping

rewards patience

easy to explain visually

aligns with long-term infrastructure use

This looks a lot like:

vesting

bond coupons

membership maturity

2ï¸âƒ£ Usage-weighted ramp
(n+1+u)

A token earns proportionally to:

how much the holder uses the system

or contributes activity

Interpretation

â€œYou earn more because you actually participate.â€

Properties

aligns incentives with real usage

kills passive speculation

perfect for:

developer tools

APIs

platforms like b0ase / Kintsugi

This is very hard to fake.

3ï¸âƒ£ Supply-weighted ramp
(n+1+s)

Eligibility increases as:

total outstanding supply grows

network adoption increases

Early tokens start small, grow as the network grows.

Interpretation

â€œYour claim strengthens as the system proves itself.â€

Properties

smooths early concentration

dampens early whales

politically attractive

more complex to explain

Why n+1+* is strictly better than n+0 or n+1
Letâ€™s be blunt:

n+0 â†’ looks like a rebate trick

n+1 â†’ clean but still abrupt

n+1+* â†’ economically honest and behaviourally sane

n+1+* gives you:

real downside

bounded upside

no free lunch

no sharp cliffs

no Ponzi optics

And crucially:

it lets price emerge gradually, not violently.

One sentence definition (blog-ready)
n+1+* schemes delay dividend eligibility and allow it to mature gradually, turning tokens from timing instruments into participation instruments.

That sentence alone will filter readers who actually understand economics from those who donâ€™t.

Why this fits b0ase / Kintsugi perfectly
Because your whole thesis is:

milestones are negotiated

contribution is mediated

value accrues through participation

not just arrival order

Binary tokens lie about that.
Fractional eligibility tells the truth.

Naming suggestion (keep it consistent)
Stick to your notation discipline:

n+1 â€” Participation Token

n+1+t â€” Maturing Participation Token

n+1+u â€” Activity-Weighted Token

n+1+s â€” Network-Weighted Token

The math stays invisible.
The logic stays legible.

Final grounding thought
Youâ€™re not designing â€œtokensâ€.

Youâ€™re designing rules for when someone is allowed to share in future flow.

n+1+* is the first version that admits:

