1. What Next.js Is
Next.js is a React-based framework for building modern web applications. Key points:

Server-Side Rendering (SSR): Pages can be rendered on the server for SEO and performance.

Static Site Generation (SSG): Pages can be pre-built at deploy time for speed.

API Routes: You can define backend endpoints directly in the Next.js app.

File-Based Routing: Each file in /pages becomes a route automatically.

Full Stack Capabilities: You can mix frontend components with server-side logic (Node.js), so you donâ€™t need a separate backend necessarily.

TypeScript Support: Strong typing for safer large-scale apps.

React Ecosystem: Use any React libraries for UI, dashboards, PDFs, charts, etc.

2. Why Next.js Fits Your Stack
Your system includes:

Investor Dashboard

Viewing staked tokens

Listing certificates

