Bit/Sign Tool

Hash PNGs

Anchor on-chain

Verify signatures

API Integration

Token staking/unstaking

Redemption

Transfers

KYC submission

On-chain verification (BSV blockchain calls)

How Next.js Handles It:
Pages & Dashboards: React components render pages; server-side or client-side as needed.

API Routes: Next.js /api/* endpoints can handle all backend logic:

Accept KYC info

Process staking

Generate certificates

Verify token ownership

Submit hashes to blockchain

PDF Generation: Can use Node libraries like pdfkit or puppeteer to generate PDFs server-side.

File Storage: PNGs and PDFs can be uploaded and served from cloud storage (S3, Hetzner, IPFS, or local server).

Security: Middleware can enforce authentication and authorization.

Blockchain Calls: Use BSV SDKs in Node.js backend to anchor hashes, verify ordinals, or track UTXOs.

3. System Architecture in Next.js Terms
/pages
  /dashboard
    index.tsx        <- Investor dashboard
    tokens.tsx       <- Token balances & staking
    certificates.tsx <- View & verify PDFs
  /bit
    /sign.tsx        <- Signature upload & verification UI
    /certificates.tsx<- Certificate generation UI

/api
  /stake.ts          <- Stake tokens
  /unstake.ts        <- Unstake tokens
  /issueCertificate.ts <- Generate certificate PDF
  /verifySignature.ts  <- Verify hash against blockchain
  /transferCertificate.ts <- Redeem / transfer
  /anchorHash.ts        <- Submit director PNG hash to blockchain
Frontend: React components for dashboards, forms, PDF previews, and token lists.

Backend: API routes interact with database, blockchain, and file storage.

Database: PostgreSQL / MySQL / MongoDB for users, token balances, certificate metadata, staking state, register of members.

Storage: Filesystem, S3, or IPFS for PNGs and PDFs.

4. Advantages
Single Stack: Frontend + backend in one framework.

Server-Side Features: PDF generation, blockchain calls, hash computation.

React Ecosystem: Use charting libraries, drag-and-drop dashboards, and other modern UI tools.

Scalable: Can deploy on Vercel, Hetzner, or any Node host.

SEO-Friendly: Only relevant if public-facing pages are needed (e.g., landing pages, blogs, courses).

5. Considerations / Caveats
Long-running Jobs: PDF generation, blockchain confirmations, and batch staking may need worker queues (Bull.js, RabbitMQ, or similar) rather than direct API route processing.

Security: KYC data and token management require strong authentication and encryption.

File Size: Large PNGs or PDFs should not be embedded directly in API routes â€” store externally and reference.

Real-Time Updates: Use WebSockets or polling for token balances / staking state on dashboards.

