2. Options for Mobile App Development
Option	Pros	Cons	Suitability
Swift (iOS) + Kotlin (Android)	Full native access, best performance, Apple Pencil / gestures	Two codebases, high dev cost	Best for MVP if App Store first, Android later
React Native	Single codebase, reuses React/Next.js knowledge, lots of crypto and PDF libraries	Slightly less performant than native, Apple Pencil features limited	Good compromise for cross-platform wallet + PDF + signature
Flutter	Single codebase, performant, beautiful UI, easy to handle gestures & PDF	Dart ecosystem may require custom bridges for BSV wallet SDK	Great for future-proof cross-platform
Capacitor / Ionic	Web-first, runs web code in app	Performance & PDF handling may be tricky	Only if minimal wallet functionality needed
Verdict:

React Native is likely the sweet spot for MVP:

Works iOS + Android.

Can fork Yours Wallet (React Native) as base.

Add custom signature canvas component + PDF viewer.

Communicate with Next.js backend for staking, certificate verification, and blockchain anchoring.

3. Handling PDFs in the Wallet
PDF Viewing

