2ï¸âƒ£ Linear curve model
A linear curve means price per token rises steadily as more tokens are sold. For example:

Option A â€” Â£100 buys 0.1% of $bWriter
0.1% = 1 million tokens (out of 1B).

Price per token = Â£100 / 1,000,000 = Â£0.0001.

Linear curve: next 1M tokens cost slightly more, next 1M slightly more, etc.

Early investors get tokens at lower price; later buyers pay progressively more.

Writers can earn tokens at the current marginal price, which starts very low but increases over time.

Option B â€” Â£100 buys 1% of $bWriter
1% = 10 million tokens.

