Register the bearer token

Stake it into a securities contract

Once staked:

the bearer token is locked

a registered position is created

the holder is added to the cap table

dividends become payable

Unstake:

registration voids

dividends stop

bearer token returns

This mirrors your earlier insight perfectly:

certificates are evidence, not ownership

Ownership lives in the register.

4. What Dividends Are Paid On
Hereâ€™s the clean rule:

Dividends are paid only on registered, staked tokens â€” not on all tokens in existence.

This solves:

infinite supply

spam

dilution

storage obligations

